<!-- Provide an overview for maintainers and reviewers. -->
## Description
Utilize flathash for iceberg equality deletes to reduce memory usage.
@dain suggested using flathash here: https://github.com/trinodb/trino/pull/21441#discussion_r1613967243

For workloads with many equality deletes, worker was OOM when loading all equality deletes into memory. Flathash reduces memory usage drastically and as a bonus the vectorized execution also appears to reduce wall clock time.

See `testLargeScaleUpsertWorkload` test for example workload of large numbers of equality deletes.
(before)
